.\" Manual page for ShellProgram
.TH SHELLPROGRAM 1 "May 2024" "Version 1.2" "Linux edition"

.SH NAME
ShellProgram \- a simple shell program

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ShellProgram

.SH DESCRIPTION
ShellProgram is a basic command-line interpreter that allows users to enter commands for execution. It provides a simple interface to the underlying operating system. This shell program reads input from the user, parses commands, and executes them in separate processes.

.SH USAGE / COMPILATION
ShellProgram operates in a loop, continually prompting for user input and executing commands. It supports basic shell functionalities. All files are to be compiled using "gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic *.c -o hsh"

.SH COMMANDS
Supported commands:
.TP
.BR exit
Exit ShellProgram. If a status is provided, it will be used as the exit status.

.SH OPTIONS
No command-line options are supported.

.SH RETURN VALUE
ShellProgram returns 0 upon successful execution. Error codes might be returned if there are issues with command execution.

.SH EXAMPLES
Running ShellProgram:
.B $ ShellProgram

.SH PATH
It will look inside all directories in the PATH environment variable for executables.

.SH SEE ALSO
bash(1), sh(1), execve(2)

